    <h2>Project Description</h2>
    <p>
      INFO0027 - Programming techniques projects: a collection of assignments covering key programming paradigms in Java, C, and Python, with an emphasis on algorithmic thinking and clean code practices.
    </p>
    <h2>Skills & Technologies</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Algorithm design in Java, C, and Python</li>
      <li>Data structures (lists, trees, hashmaps)</li>
      <li>Modular programming and Makefile automation</li>
      <li>Testing, debugging, and performance analysis</li>
      <li>Collaborative software development</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Code Logic</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Each assignment implements a key algorithm or data structure from scratch (e.g., sorting, trees, graph traversals).</li>
      <li>Emphasis on modular code, with reusable functions and classes.</li>
      <li>Makefiles automate compilation and testing for C/Java projects.</li>
      <li>Python scripts focus on readability and rapid prototyping.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Sample Code</h2>
    <pre><code>// Example: Binary search tree insertion in C
void insert_bst(node_t **root, int value) {
    if (!*root) {
        *root = malloc(sizeof(node_t));
        (*root)->value = value;
        (*root)->left = (*root)->right = NULL;
    } else if (value &lt; (*root)->value) {
        insert_bst(&(*root)->left, value);
    } else {
        insert_bst(&(*root)->right, value);
    }
}
    </code></pre>
    <h2>Results & Impact</h2>
